<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-321-792  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 321 792.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Communications  March 1990 v13 n2 p108(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New 3D graphical presentation of the ISO transport protocol.andO;(International Standards Organization) (technical article)(tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poo, Gee-Swee; Ang, Wilson.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A new graphical presentation of the ISO transport protocol isproposed in this paper.andP;  The states, events and actions arerepresented by a set of icons which give rise to athree-dimensional effect in the protocol structure.andP;  The emphasisis on the ability to demonstrate the end-to-end logical flow ofestablishing, maintaining and releasing transport connectionsbetween two transport entities.andP;  Compared with the conventionalflat static display of the state diagram, the new presentationmakes it easier to visualize and comprehend the abstract conceptof the transport mechanism.andP;  The idea is implemented on an IBM PCAT using the GKS graphics systems.andP;  The software provides not onlyprogram-controlled demonstrations on connection sequences, butalso displays of dynamic reconfiguration of protocols through userinteraction.andP;  (Reprinted by permission of the publisher.)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     StandardsTransport Layer ControlProtocolISOThree-Dimensional GraphicsModelsTutorialTheoretical Approach.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartphotograph.andO;Caption:   Conventional state diagram. (chart)Graphical picture of a state transition diagram of a transportconnection. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>